"{    \"translations\": [        {            \"english_version\": \"President Joe Biden announced that Israel agreed to stop military activities in Gaza during Ramadan, starting on March 10th. The ceasefire is expected to be in place by next Monday. Efforts by America, Egypt, and Qatar aim to secure a deal where Hamas would release Israeli hostages in exchange for a pause in fighting and increased aid to Gaza.\",            \"english_title\": \"Israel-Gaza Ceasefire\",            \"translated_version\": \"El Presidente Joe Biden anunci\u00f3 que Israel acord\u00f3 detener las actividades militares en Gaza durante el Ramad\u00e1n, a partir del 10 de marzo. Se espera que el alto el fuego est\u00e9 en vigor para el pr\u00f3ximo lunes. Los esfuerzos de Estados Unidos, Egipto y Qatar buscan asegurar un acuerdo donde Hamas liberar\u00eda rehenes israel\u00edes a cambio de una pausa en los combates y m\u00e1s ayuda para Gaza.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Israel-Gaza Ceasefire\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"European and allied leaders, after a meeting in Paris, did not reach a consensus on sending troops to Ukraine. While French President Macron did not rule out the possibility, Germany's Chancellor Scholz stated that European and NATO countries had decided against sending soldiers to Ukrainian soil.\",            \"english_title\": \"European Response to Ukraine Crisis\",            \"translated_version\": \"Los l\u00edderes europeos y aliados, despu\u00e9s de una reuni\u00f3n en Par\u00eds, no llegaron a un consenso sobre enviar tropas a Ucrania. Mientras que el Presidente franc\u00e9s Macron no descart\u00f3 la posibilidad, la Canciller de Alemania Scholz afirm\u00f3 que los pa\u00edses europeos y de la OTAN hab\u00edan decidido no enviar soldados a suelo ucraniano.\",            \"translated_title\": \"European Response to Ukraine Crisis\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"The European Union parliament approved a bill for environmental conservation, requiring EU countries to restore 20% of land and sea areas by 2030. However, this legislation has faced opposition from Europe's farmers who argue that restrictions on chemicals and greenhouse-gas emissions would harm their livelihoods.\",            \"english_title\": \"Environmental Conservation Bill in EU\",            \"translated_version\": \"El parlamento de la Uni\u00f3n Europea aprob\u00f3 una ley para la conservaci\u00f3n del medio ambiente, que requiere que los pa\u00edses de la UE restauren el 20% de las \u00e1reas terrestres y marinas para el 2030. Sin embargo, esta legislaci\u00f3n ha enfrentado oposici\u00f3n de los agricultores europeos que argumentan que las restricciones a los qu\u00edmicos y emisiones de gases de efecto invernadero perjudicar\u00edan sus medios de vida.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Environmental Conservation Bill in EU\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Oleg Orlov, a human-rights campaigner in Russia, was sentenced to two and a half years in prison for criticizing Russia's war in Ukraine. Orlov, a co-chair of the Memorial Human Rights Centre, accused Russian troops of mass murder in Ukraine.\",            \"english_title\": \"Human Rights Activist Sentenced in Russia\",            \"translated_version\": \"Oleg Orlov, un defensor de los derechos humanos en Rusia, fue sentenciado a dos a\u00f1os y medio de prisi\u00f3n por criticar la guerra de Rusia en Ucrania. Orlov, co-presidente del Centro de Derechos Humanos Memorial, acus\u00f3 a las tropas rusas de asesinato en masa en Ucrania.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Human Rights Activist Sentenced in Russia\"        },        {            \"english_version\": \"Members of the Nigeria Labour Congress protested nationwide against the government's economic policies. The trade unions demanded wage increases and criticized the handling of inflation and the removal of a popular fuel subsidy.\",            \"english_title\": \"Trade Union Protests in Nigeria\",            \"translated_version\": \"Los miembros del Congreso de Trabajo de Nigeria protestaron en todo el pa\u00eds contra las pol\u00edticas econ\u00f3micas del gobierno. Los sindicatos exigieron aumentos salariales y criticaron la gesti\u00f3n de la inflaci\u00f3n y la eliminaci\u00f3n de un popular subsidio al combustible.\",            \"translated_title\": \"Trade Union Protests in Nigeria\"        }    ]}"